28/09/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The European Commission (EC) wants adjustments in Macedonia's election laws by the end of this year, it indicated during talks Tuesday (27 September) with a Macedonian delegation. The EC representatives stressed the need to strengthen measures ahead of the 2006 parliamentary elections, to avoid a repetition of irregularities that occurred this year. 
In other news, Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski and British counterpart Tony Blair were due to hold talks Wednesday on Macedonia's bid to join Euro-Atlantic structures. Britain currently holds the rotating EU presidency. (Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax - 28/09/05; A1 TV - 27/09/05)
